irst Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[{"name":"Anne","meanings":["A name corrpted from Hannah, q.v. It is also found several times in a male name. From Ann, Anne, we have as nicknames Nan and Nancy"]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Anna Priol was born in 1294, in Augsburg, Augsburg, Bavaria, Germany as the daughter of Heinrich Priol and Hildegarde Priol. She married Johannes Goldochs II. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died before 13 July 1351, in her hometown."},"et":{"1294–vor 13. Juli 1351":"1294–enne 13. juulit 1351","1294–1351":"1294–1351","1288–1344":"1288–1344","1320–1347":"1320–1347","1270–1325":"1270–1325","–Female":"Surnud","1347":"1347","1325":"1325","21 September 1325":"21. september 1325","1344":"1344","1288":"1288","1320":"1320","1351":"1351","vor 13. Juli 1351":"enne 13. juulit 1351","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","Augsburg, Augsburg, Bayern, Deutschland":"Augsburg, Augsburg, Bayern, Saksamaa","Augsburg, Augsburg, Bavaria, Germany":"Augsburg, Augsburg, Bayern, Saksamaa","Augsburg, Schwaben, Bayern, Germany":"Augsburg, Augsburg, Bayern, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1294–vor 13. Juli 1351":"1294–ennen vuotta 13. heinäkuuta 1351","1294–1351":"1294–1351","1288–1344":"1288–1344","1320–1347":"1320–1347","1270–1325":"1270–1325","–Female":"Kuollut","1347":"1347","1325":"1325","21 September 1325":"21. syyskuuta 1325","1344":"1344","1288":"1288","1320":"1320","1351":"1351","vor 13. Juli 1351":"ennen vuotta 13. heinäkuuta 1351","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","Augsburg, Augsburg, Bayern, Deutschland":"Augsbur